---
title: Creamy Caramelized Onion Meatloaves with Sumac Roasted Asparagus & Zucchini
description: Glaze ‘em, smother ‘em, stuff ‘em—meatloaves really can do it all. These loaves mix things up with a spoonful of creamy sauce over top, made with sweet caramelized onion, cream cheese, butter, and a pinch of parsley. On the side, sumac—a tangy Middle Eastern spice—seasons carrots and zucchini with citrusy flavor (similar to lemon zest!). Serve it all together, letting the sauce pool around the veggies, for a perfectly paired plate and yet another meatloaf miracle.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67b400a42ccb8b03ddc1173d-0a901471.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67b55d567ee49499a5e3d3a3-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 52 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 25 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 860 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-caramelized-onion-meatloaves-67b55d567ee49499a5e3d3a3
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1-inch-thick half-moons.

Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and discard bottom 1 inch from @asparagus{6%oz}; cut into 1-inch pieces.

> Save carrots for another use.

In a #medium bowl{}, gently combine @ground beef{10%oz}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{3/4%tsp} (1 1⁄4 tsp for 4), and @pepper{}.

Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (four loaves for 4).

Place meatloaves on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. TIP: Line sheet with foil first for easier cleanup.

Toss carrots on empty side with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 baking sheets; roast meatloaves on middle rack and carrots on top rack.

Roast on top rack until meatloaves are cooked through and carrots are browned and tender, ~{22-25%minutes}. TIP: Love extra-crispy veggies? Once meatloaves are done, remove from sheet and continue roasting carrots for ~{2-3%minutes} more.

While everything roasts, halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Pick @parsley{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; roughly chop leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes} (7-10 minutes for 4 servings). Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Add a large drizzle of oil to same pan over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{6-9%minutes}. TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if onion begins to brown too quickly.

Add @cream cheese{2%tbsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup}, and @sugar{3/4%tsp} (1 1⁄2 tsp for 4 servings) to pan with onion; cook until thickened, ~{1-3%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) and a pinch of chopped parsley. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Carefully toss zucchini and carrots together with half the @sumac{1%tsp} (all for 4 servings).

Divide meatloaves and carrots and zucchini between plates. Spoon caramelized onion sauce over meatloaves; garnish with remaining chopped parsley. Serve.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.